Correctly extract any file paths from a form value.

These attributes can be in the from DW&#95;AT&#95;decl&#95;file or DW&#95;AT&#95;call&#95;file attributes. We need to use the file index in the correct <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfunit">DWARFUnit</a>&#39;s line table prologue, and each <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfformvalue">DWARFFormValue</a> has the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarfunit">DWARFUnit</a> the form value was extracted from.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Kind">The kind of path to extract.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

</SectionUser>

### skipValue() {#a4b10b1371b2d1f535ff65cf1aeed3158}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool DWARFFormValue::skipValue (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/dwarf/#a6c06a10ffac779879f6b62a1a904517b">dwarf::Form</a> Form, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dataextractor">DataExtractor</a> DebugInfoData, uint64&#95;t &#42; OffsetPtr, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/dwarf/formparams">dwarf::FormParams</a> FormParams)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Skip a form&#39;s value in <code>DebugInfoData</code> at the offset specified by <code>OffsetPtr</code>.

Skips the bytes for the specified form and updates the offset.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Form">The DW&#95;FORM enumeration that indicates the form to skip.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="DebugInfoData">The data where we want to skip the value.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="OffsetPtr">A reference to the offset that will be updated.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="FormParams">DWARF parameters to help interpret forms.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
true on success, false if the form was not skipped.
</SectionUser>
